                <h2>Business flows</h2>
                <h3>🎁<span style="width: 17px;" class="oe-tabs"> </span>​Loyalty program</h3>
                <p>
                A great way to get your customers to come back to your store or your eCommerce is to&nbsp;reward them based on their previous purchases. Use the&nbsp;
                <strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">Discount &amp; Loyalty</font></strong> feature&nbsp;to set up&nbsp;loyalty programs such as free products, discounts, or free shipping.
                </p>
                <p>
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/4524?fullscreen=1" class="btn btn-secondary mb-2">🎓 Tutorial</a>&nbsp;
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/documentation/latest/applications/sales/sales/products_prices/loyalty_discount.html" class="btn btn-secondary mb-2">📖 Documentation</a>
                </p>
                <div class="o_editor_banner o_not_editable lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-success pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-protected="true">
                <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal">🚀</i>
                <div class="w-100 px-3" data-oe-protected="false">
                        <h4>Demo: Sell in-store and give your customer a free product</h4>
                        <p>The <em>loyalty card</em> program grants <em>loyalty points</em> based on the purchase.&nbsp;You can then exchange these points for a reward.</p>
                        <ul>
                        <li>In Point of Sale, open the <em>Shop</em> register.</li>
                        <li>Select a customer and add products for a minimum of $50.</li>
                        <li>Click on the <em>Reward</em> button, then select <em>Free Product - 12 coloring pencils</em>.</li>
                        <li>Click on <em>Payment</em>&nbsp;and finalize the checkout.</li>
                        </ul>
                </div>
                </div>
                <p><br /></p>
                <h3>🔎<span style="width: 17px;" class="oe-tabs"> </span>​Add characteristics&nbsp;on your products' web pages</h3>
                <p>
                By default, <strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">attributes</font></strong> are used to create <strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">product variants</font></strong>&nbsp;based on characteristics such as&nbsp;color
                (see the product <em>Micro scooter</em> as an example).
                </p>
                <p>
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/2723?fullscreen=1" class="btn btn-secondary">🎓 Tutorial</a>&nbsp;
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/documentation/latest/applications/websites/ecommerce/products/variants.html" class="btn btn-secondary">📖 Documentation</a><br />
                </p>
                <p>
                Informative characteristics, such as the brand, the minimum age required, and number of players, are also defined as <strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">attributes</font></strong>&nbsp;on the product form. However,
                each&nbsp;attribute must be correctly set up before adding values to avoid creating new product variants. To do so, set the attribute's&nbsp;<em>Variants Creation Mode</em> field to&nbsp;<em>Never (option)</em>.
                </p>
                <p>Characteristics&nbsp;with multiple values, such as the number of players, should be added multiple times: one attribute line per value. This ensures a proper display on the products' pages.</p>
                <p><img class="img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" src="/web/image/toy_store.ir_attachment_1049" /></p>
                <p><br /></p>
                <h3>🔄<span style="width: 17px;" class="oe-tabs"> </span>​Automatic replenishment</h3>
                <p>
                With thousands of products to manage,&nbsp;automizing product replenishment saves you time and prevents&nbsp;stock shortages. Set <strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">reordering rules</font></strong>&nbsp;to automatically
                generate purchase orders when product quantities fall below specified levels. Use the <strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">replenishment</font></strong> tool to review and validate these purchase orders before confirming
                them.
                </p>
                <p>
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/5378?fullscreen=1" class="btn btn-secondary mb-2">🎓 Tutorial</a>
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/documentation/latest/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/product_management/product_replenishment/reordering_rules.html" class="btn btn-secondary mb-2">📖 Documentation</a>
                </p>
                <div class="o_editor_banner o_not_editable lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-success pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-protected="true">
                <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal">🚀</i>
                <div class="w-100 px-3" data-oe-protected="false">
                        <h4>Demo: automize the replenishment of the game "Pandemic"</h4>
                        <p>
                        <span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
                                Adjust the&nbsp;<em>Reordering Rule</em>&nbsp;for the&nbsp;<em>Pandemic game</em>&nbsp;so that when the stock quantity drops below 5, Odoo automatically creates&nbsp;a purchase order to replenish the stock to 15 games.
                        </span>
                        <br />
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                        <li>
                                Go to&nbsp;
                                <em>
                                Inventory&nbsp;
                                <em style="text-align: inherit; font-family: var(--body-font-family); font-size: var(--body-font-size); font-weight: var(--body-font-weight);">
                                        → Operations <em style="text-align: inherit; font-family: var(--body-font-family); font-size: var(--body-font-size); font-weight: var(--body-font-weight);">→ Replenishment</em>
                                </em>
                                </em>
                                .
                        </li>
                        <li>Review the reordering rule for <em>Pandemic</em>&nbsp;and change the <em>Max</em>&nbsp;quantity to 15.</li>
                        <li>Click on&nbsp;<span class="fa fa-refresh"></span><em>&nbsp;Automate</em>.</li>
                        <li>Review the new draft Purchase Order.</li>
                        </ul>
                </div>
                </div>
                <p><br /></p>
                <h3>🚚<span style="width: 17px;" class="oe-tabs"> </span>​Receive products from a purchase order</h3>
                <p>
                <strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">Purchase orders</font></strong> simplify&nbsp;
                <span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
                        communication with vendors and tracking of ordered products.&nbsp;<strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">Inventory operations</font></strong> confirm the reception or delivery of products and update&nbsp;
                </span>
                stock levels.
                </p>
                <p>
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/5316?fullscreen=1" class="btn btn-secondary">🎓 Tutorial</a>&nbsp;
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/documentation/latest/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/shipping_receiving/daily_operations/shipments_deliveries.html" class="btn btn-secondary">📖 Documentation</a><br />
                </p>
                <div class="o_editor_banner o_not_editable lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-success pb-0 pt-3" data-oe-protected="true">
                <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal">🚀</i>
                <div class="w-100 px-3" data-oe-protected="false">
                        <h4>Demo:&nbsp;receive products and update the stock levels</h4>
                        <ul>
                        <li>Go to <em>Purchase</em>&nbsp;and open the order&nbsp;<em>P00001</em>.</li>
                        <li>Click​ on <em>Receive Products</em></li>
                        <li><em>Validate</em>&nbsp;the receipt<br /></li>
                        </ul>
                </div>
                </div>
                <p><br /></p>
                <h3>🧮<span style="width: 17px;" class="oe-tabs"> </span>​Seasonal physical&nbsp;inventory&nbsp;count</h3>
                <p>
                In many countries, ensuring inventory accuracy is a legal requirement. Use the&nbsp;<strong><font style="color: rgb(113, 75, 103);">Physical Inventory</font></strong>​ feature in the Inventory app or&nbsp;the Barcode app to ease and
                speed up the process.
                </p>
                <div data-oe-protected="true" class="o_editor_banner o_not_editable lh-1 d-flex align-items-center alert alert-info pb-0 pt-3">
                <i class="o_editor_banner_icon mb-3 fst-normal">💡</i>
                <div data-oe-protected="false" class="w-100 px-3">
                        <p>Use the Barcode app on mobile devices&nbsp;to scan products with the&nbsp;integrated camera. To speed up the inventory count, split the workload between several people using their personal devices.</p>
                </div>
                </div>
                <p>
                <a href="https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/695" class="btn btn-secondary mb-2">🎓 Barcode tutorial</a>&nbsp;
